arcade literature the humanities and the world home join login blogs multimedia publications seminars rss about saturday march 17 2012 arcade home colloquies sociology of reading colloquy welcome to colloquies with a scope as broad as literature humanities the world arcade can seem bewilderingly freewheeling colloquies are our way of bringing into relief the recurring questions themes and ideas that run through arcade across time and across the spectrum from blogs to multimedia to articles it's our hope that these colloquies will help to reveal the conversations between less formal genres like the blog post and lengthier and perhaps more traditional meditations instead of arranging these groups along strictly disciplinary lines we ve chosen to highlight theoretical foci that cut across historical periods and geographic regions because we are not subject to the constraints of print runs the colloquies are dynamic and new items are continually being added to them for each colloquy we ve asked one of the scholars who participate in arcade to write a short introduction many thanks to all those who have contributed natalia cecire august 2011 browse colloquies colloquy introduced by first posted the sociology of reading anne dewitt 03 05 2012 8 26am global networks meredith ramirez talusan 02 01 2012 8 26am gesture claire jarvis 01 01 2012 9 25pm occupy david palumbo liu 12 04 2011 10 29pm nostalgia mourning disappearance joel burges 11 01 2011 8 32am gender and feminisms cecile alduy 10 01 2011 7 43am autonomy andrew goldstone 08 31 2011 9 23pm the contemporary novel lee konstantinou 08 04 2011 9 30am nostalgia mourning disappearance gesture occupy nostalgia mourning disappearance gender and feminisms autonomy the contemporary novel dlcl logo privacy policy terms of use dmca contact stanford strives to post only content for which we have licensed permission or that is otherwise permitted by copyright law if you have a concern that your copyrighted material is posted here